<item>
            <title>[SPARK-747] Throw an exception on slaves if a message is sent that is larger than akka&apos;s max frame size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-747</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This can be really hard to debug for users, until we fix &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-669&quot; title=&quot;Send back task results through BlockManager instead of Akka messages&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-669&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-669&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we should at least warn users when this happens with an exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/spark-users/WG87fG8rrKY/6VpJ1AFXS-cJ&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://groups.google.com/forum/#!msg/spark-users/WG87fG8rrKY/6VpJ1AFXS-cJ&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12704754">SPARK-747</key>
